In East Rainton (p. 101) the demesnes are demised to four tenants for a term of yearS, under conditions which were probably usual in similar (101111808, viz„ to manure a certain proportion of the land each year, to leave the buildings as they received them, and the land, as to the ploughing, as they entered, to grind their corn at the lord's mill, as they were liable to grind who held husbandry lands.
